title: Grateful Dead Live at Saratoga Performing Arts Center on 1985-06-27
lineage: DAT playback on Sony PCM-R500 > unbalanced XLR analog outputs > Neutrik inputs, Presonus Firebox  (pre-amplification and analog-to-digital) > firewire > PC/WinXP Pro > recorded to 24 bit/96 KHz WAV using Wavelab 5 > mastered with Waves L3 Multimaximizer > rendered to 16/44.1 using Waves IDR (type I dither/ultra shaping) > tracked with CDWAV 1.9 > FLAC
taper: DAT kindly provided for transfer by M.Townshend

reviews.review_text: This SBD sounds the best My opinion, but I've listened to them all.  Great job.

Great show Great copy We used to listen to this tape all the time driving around on Dead Tour.  The show is awesome and this recording is great, I LOVE the Johnny B Goode, Baby Blue Encore, perfect caper to the show.

Great Show I happen to love '85 shows and this one is no exception. Great recording of a lively performance. Love the Crazy Fingers>Supplication>High Time in the first set as well as the Truckin'>Spoonful>Black Peter in the second set.

Toga..Toga..Toga I started seeing the Dead in 83'So I'm partial to 85'LOVED IT This show is in my top 5 for the year.Tons of energy in the 1st set.I absolutely love the Crazy Fingers>Supplication Jam>High Time!!!SICK You can hear Lazy Lightning>>> Teases,every time I hear I get lost!So I just listen to the music play.The 2nd set is solid,the Stranger>Eyes is ever so nice!Spoonful and the double encore of Johnny B. Goode & It's All Over Now,Baby Blue added to a entirely great show.THE SOUND QUALITY is TOPPS!!!!!!
one of the best of all time setlists/performances
Great show and Great sound! Wish I had been there. The boys were on. Baby Blue! Love that Stranger!

A liitle bit higher Well, this was my first summer tour shows and what a blast.
In the summer of '85' the Dead had the intensity level dialed way up.
These shows were not slow and plodding they were fast and explosive.  The Dead came ready to play and they moved from tune to tune with ease.
I was completely hooked and was already making plans to go to see the Dead play some place called RED Rocks!!!
